thread.title: LHS volleyball goes 0-3 at Washburn Rural
thread.title_full: LHS volleyball goes 0-3 at Washburn Rural

author: Staff Reports
title: LHS volleyball goes 0-3 at Washburn Rural
text:
Advertisement 
Topeka  Lawrence High’s volleyball team dropped three matches Tuesday at the Washburn Rural quadragular. 
The Lions fell to Washburn Rural, 25-14, 25-13, Manhattan, 25-19, 25-12, and Topeka Hayden, 25-12, 25-14. 
Among the leaders for LHS were Lexi Anglin with eight kills and six blocks, Kyleigh Severa with seven kills and seven digs, Amelia Dunlap with seven kills, Olivia Morgan with seven kills, Nicole Owens with 11 digs, Katie Murrish with seven digs, Nico Kenney with eight digs, and Laurel Bird with 31 assists. 
The Lions will play Saturday at Emporia.
